  "title": "Expose onBlur, onFocus, onKeyDown events out of SearchBox",
  "body": "**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature for SearchBox\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nAll provided features are good for me, I don't need to create my custom one.\r\n- I use this SearchBox for a Dashboard page, and also Auto Complete.\r\n```js\r\n<Layout>\r\n  <Header>\r\n    <SearchBox />\r\n    <AutocompleteResults />\r\n  </Header>\r\n  <Content />\r\n</Layout>\r\n```\r\n- Actually, I don't need react-autosuggest, as I tried your examples.\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your proposed API entry? The new option to add? What is the behavior?**\r\nWhen using this Search Box, I need to know whether users focus/ blur/ press keys (Up, Down, Enter, ...) to implement my own AutoComplete features.\r\nThe solution could be inputProps (type = object) property.\r\n\r\n**What project are you opening an issue for?**\r\n- react-instantsearch\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\n3.1.0\r\n\r\nWhat do you think @vvo?\r\nLike https://github.com/vinhlh/instantsearch.js/commit/14cca027cc49e8d3ee23aba02f151e07ac2f61c1",
